				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First off, this is a great site and I look forward to joining the fun as my journey begins anew as a member of one of the most special classes EQ has to offer.
<br />

<br />
Not sure if this is the correct forum for this, but since my question is concerning classes that can use the item it seemed right.
<br />

<br />
Why can the other leather classes (DRU, MNK) use this great quest item with WIS, STA, raw HP and summoned hammers that we have the skill to throw while we can't?
<br />

<br />
I could see it being considered "overpowered" if we had access to regular tools for rooting/snaring mobs but not all of us can knock over Tunare and get at her stash of goodies.
<br />

<br />
How hard could it be to change the item description for the Bracer and the Shattering Hammers so we can use it?
<br />

<br />
If I wanted damage from ready summoned throwing items I'd get a Dusty Soriz Worker Pouch (which we can use /boggle) and cut loose.
<br />

<br />
I want the stats more than the hammers but there aren't a lot of well-balanced wrist pieces that are be relatively available to our community.
<br />

<br />
This one just doesn't make sense to me. 
<br />

<br />
I didn't find much on this using the search but I don't always have the best luck with them so I'll apologize in advance if this subject has been beaten to death and I missed all the fun.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for any insight anyone can provide on this.<br />_________________<br />Chakuliz, Scaled Beastial Warden of Cabilis
<br />
FV Server
<br />

<br />
"Call me a Monk again and I'll show you how far this Sambata War Staff can really go...."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
